title: Samsung Galaxy C9 Pro with 6-inch display and 6GB RAM launching in India on January 18th
text:
Samsung Galaxy C9 Pro with 6-inch display and 6GB RAM launching in... Samsung Galaxy C9 Pro with 6-inch display and 6GB RAM launching in India on January 18th By - January 12, 2017 “Samsung’s first smartphone to boast 6GB of RAM, the Galaxy C9 Pro, is coming to India next week” 
Samsung has sent out invites for a product launch event in India on January 18th, where the brand will be launching the Galaxy C9 Pro in the country. The phone was unveiled in China in October last year as the company’s first smartphone to boast 6GB of RAM. In China, the phone is available at the equivalent of Rs 31,500, and is expected to be priced in the same range in India. 
To recap the specs, the Samsung Galaxy C9 Pro features a metal unibody design and a fingerprint sensor hidden in its home button. It comes with a huge 6-inch full HD Super AMOLED display, and is powered by a Qualcomm Snapdragon 653 SoC. The phone offers 64GB of storage, 16MP cameras in the front and back, Android Marshmallow, and a beefy 4,000mAh battery. Facebook Comments
